---
title: Chicken, White Bean & Kale Caesar Salad with Dark Meat Chicken, Broccoli & Garlicky Panko
description: Our chefs' riff on a vegan Caesar salad is sure to check all the boxes. You’ll pair a base of kale, white beans, and roasted broccoli with a creamy dressing featuring vegan Worcestershire sauce, lemon, mustard, and nutritional yeast—a flavor powerhouse that helps simulate the nutty, cheesy flavor of Parm, minus the dairy. A shower of crispy garlic panko and ciabatta toast points complete the meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6864f18e0203e9f8dbb4c868-46a27bc8.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6864f18e0203e9f8dbb4c868-en-US.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 980 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 18 g
  sodium: 1590 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-white-bean-and-kale-caesar-salad-6864f18e0203e9f8dbb4c868
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @broccoli{1%unit} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Remove and discard
any large stems from @kale{4%ounce} if necessary; chop into bite-size pieces.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%unit}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{2%tsp}(for 2 servings), @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly browned,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Place kale in a #large bowl{}; add a drizzle of @olive oil{}(large drizzle for 4
servings) and a pinch of salt. Using your hands, massage until leaves are
tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil(large drizzle for 4 servings) in a #small pan{}
over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until
golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in lemon zest, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @nutritional
yeast{1%tbsp}, a pinch of salt, and pepper. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @vegan mayonnaise{4%tbsp},
@dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @nutritional yeast{1%tbsp},
@worcestershire sauce{1%tsp}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Set aside.

> Save any remaining Worcestershire sauce for another use.

Halve @ciabatta bread{1%unit} and toast until golden brown.

Lightly drizzle cut sides with @olive oil{} and @salt{} and @pepper{}. Halve on a
diagonal.

To bowl with kale, add broccoli, beans, and dressing; toss to combine. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide salad between #plates{}. Top with toasted panko and @?korean chili
flakes{1%tsp} as many as you like. Serve with ciabatta points and remaining
lemon wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.